[% META title = "Hive Management System" %]
[% PageVersion = 'Apiary/hive_management.tt,v 0.02 2026/03/17 shanta Exp shanta' %]
[% IF debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="app-container">

    <div class="page-header">
        <h1>Hive Management System</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">Track and manage your hives through every season.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="content-primary">

            <div class="app-section">
                <p>Welcome to the Hive Management System. This system helps beekeepers track inspections, monitor colony strength, and plan seasonal activities.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="app-section">
                <h2>Hive Inspection Checklist</h2>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <p>During each inspection, record observations for:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Queen presence and laying pattern</li>
                        <li>Brood pattern and development stages</li>
                        <li>Food stores — honey and pollen frames</li>
                        <li>Population strength (frames of bees)</li>
                        <li>Disease and pest signs</li>
                        <li>Equipment condition</li>
                        <li>Space requirements</li>
                        <li>Swarm indicators (queen cells, overcrowding)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="app-section">
                <h2>Seasonal Management</h2>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <h3>Spring</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Clean and inspect equipment after winter</li>
                        <li>Assess colony strength and survival</li>
                        <li>Feed if food stores are low</li>
                        <li>Manage for swarm prevention</li>
                        <li>Add supers as colony expands</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <h3>Summer</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Monitor honey flow progress</li>
                        <li>Add honey supers before they are needed</li>
                        <li>Manage ventilation during heat</li>
                        <li>Monitor Varroa mite levels</li>
                        <li>Harvest honey at peak ripeness</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <h3>Fall</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Assess and top up food stores</li>
                        <li>Treat for Varroa mites</li>
                        <li>Reduce entrances to prevent robbing</li>
                        <li>Combine weak colonies if needed</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <h3>Winter</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Insulate hives appropriately for your climate</li>
                        <li>Ensure adequate upper ventilation</li>
                        <li>Protect from prevailing winds</li>
                        <li>Monitor food stores through winter checks</li>
                        <li>Clear entrances of snow or debris</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="app-section">
                <h2>Hive Records</h2>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <p>Keeping detailed records is essential for successful beekeeping. For each hive, track:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Queen information — age, source, performance</li>
                        <li>Inspection dates and key findings</li>
                        <li>Treatments applied and dates</li>
                        <li>Feeding records</li>
                        <li>Honey harvest amounts</li>
                        <li>Equipment additions or changes</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><em>Digital hive record keeping system coming soon.</em></p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="app-section">
                <h2>View Hives by Yard</h2>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <div class="form-container">
                        <form action="/Apiary/hives_for_yard" method="get" class="app-form">
                            <div class="form-row">
                                <div class="form-field">
                                    <label for="yard_id">Yard ID:</label>
                                    <input type="text" name="yard_id" id="yard_id" class="form-input" placeholder="Enter yard ID">
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="form-actions">
                                <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">View Hives</button>
                            </div>
                        </form>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="page-footer">
                <div class="footer-actions">
                    <a href="/Apiary" class="btn btn-secondary">Back to Apiary Management</a>
                    <a href="/BMaster" class="btn btn-secondary">Back to BMaster Home</a>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

</div>
